  "title": "IInterferenceDetectionMgr.TreatSubAssembliesAsComponents",
  "description": "Gets or sets whether to treat subassemblies as single components so that interferences between a sub-assembly's components are not reported.",
  "signature": "System.Boolean TreatSubAssembliesAsComponents {get; set;}",
  "parameters": [],
  "returns": "True to treat a sub-assembly's components as single, false to not",
  "remarks": "Currently, the value set for this property:\nexists only while the InterferenceDetectionMgr object is in scope; i.e., setting this property is temporary.\ndoes not persist across SOLIDWORKS Design sessions.\ndoes not persist into the next invocation of interference detection in the user interface.",
